{% extends "base.twig" %}

{% block pagetitle %}Presence{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <div id="centered">
        <header>
            <h1><a href="{{ app.url_generator.generate('homepage') }}">&#x21F6;</a> Presence</h1>
        </header>

        <article>

            <p>This tool shows the availabilities of teams, generated from the Google calendar entries.</p>

            <h2>How to use with Google calendar</h2>

            <ul class="typeList">
                <li><a href="#entryHoliday" class="timeSlotBubble off">Holiday entry</a></li>
                <li><a href="#entryOff" class="timeSlotBubble off">Off entry</a></li>
                <li><a href="#entryLocation"  class="timeSlotBubble busy">Location entry</a></li>
                <li><a href="#entryNormal" class="timeSlotBubble busy">Event entry</a></li>
                <li><a class="timeSlotBubble available">Free</a></li>
            </ul>

            <h3 id="entryHoliday">&#x21F6; Holiday entry <a class="top" href="#centered">#top</a></h3>

            <p>To display a day as on holiday, a <b>#holiday</b> tag has to be added to the event summary.</p>

            <p>The holiday entries can be inserted as full-day (multiple as well) or time period calendar entries.</p>

            <p>Example: Ibiza #holiday</p>

            <h3 id="entryOff">&#x21F6; Off entry <a class="top" href="#centered">#top</a></h3>

            <p>For days off which are not booked on holiday, use the <b>#off</b> tag.</p>

            <p>The holiday entries can be inserted as full-day (multiple as well) or time period calendar entries.</p>

            <p>Example: University #off</p>

            <h3 id="entryLocation">&#x21F6; Location entry <a class="top" href="#centered">#top</a></h3>

            <p>If you spend the day away from your default location, use the <b>@location</b> tag.</p>

            <p>Location entries should only be inserted as full-day events.</p>

            <p>Example: @LS</p>

            <h3 id="entryNormal">&#x21F6; Event entry <a class="top" href="#centered">#top</a></h3>

            <p>Every entry, having a period of more than 15 minutes, is displayed in the event list.</p>

            <p>Moreover, the morning and afternoon periods are marked busy if event is inserted:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Entries beginning <b>before 12pm</b>, mark the morning period busy (orange).</li>
                <li>Entries ending <b>after 12pm</b>, mark the afternoon period busy (orange).</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Printing tricks</h2>

            <h3 class="printScale">&#x21F6; Fit on single page <a class="top" href="#centered">#top</a></h3>

            <p>Sometimes it happens that there are too many members, so that the print page does not fit on one page. To make it fit you can scale the printing page:</p>

            <h4>Using Google Chrome</h4>
            <ul class="typeList">
                <li>Print using system dialog... ( &#x2325;&#x2318;P )</li>
                <li>Scale XX%</li>
            </ul>

        </article>

        <footer>
            <a href="#centered">#top</a>
        </footer>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
